<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Plenty of people have been turned away from joining a guild because they are not a needed class for that guild. The most often used example is the fact Afterlife listed on their guildpage for a year they were not recruiting any paladins (because they were useless on raids).<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
They aren't saying that now are they? In the past knights were gimped we can agree on that, the argument however centre's around the current situation not the past. These days knights are a much more viable class.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Perhaps it is the exception, but most of the people in my guild spend most of their online time raiding, not doing exp groups. When your guild raids 10 hours a day or more, there is not a lot of time left over for exp grouping.<br>
<br>
For what I do, desirablity for a raid is much more important than how desirable you are in an exp group.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
To be your best for raiding you need 65 and various AA's, raid exp is not a very rapid means of getting those levels/AA. If your guild raids 10 hours a day that would seem to suggest that you only have limited time available to exp you don't really want to be LFG too long right? <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>What I said was if you assume that you cannot be perfect, and get them 100% balanced, then it makes sense to make one better at raids and the other better in exp groups, rather than one class better at both. Do you really disagree with this?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yes actually I do. Make any group dependant class undesirable to group with and all he can do is sit on his hands, thats the concern being addressed in this thread. Raiding cannot be placed on one side of the scale with exp on the other, it doesn't work like that.<br>
<br>
Raids are a group effort and everybody usually has a part to play in the success or failure of the guild - being the offtanker/group healer/DA mob positioner etc may be considered less glamorous than the main tank position but those jobs and others that knights perform admirably are no less vital to the guilds success. i'm level 62 in a guild with 6 warriors level 65 and numerous AA's guess I need to exp some eh?<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I am not saying this as an excuse, I would feel the same way if paladins were needed on raids more and less useful in exp groups than warriors<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
To be perfectly frank I'm not sure I believe you.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I can not think of a single boss mob that we do which I could tank on a raid. Can I off tank adds and such? Yes, I can. But the main bosses? No, I cannot. Could I tank some things we finished with 6 months or more ago, sure, probably, but those encounters are beneath us in the challenge involved, we have moved on. I think you will find in most guilds that only warriors are able to tank the hard bosses they are fighting, whatever they are. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
...and I think you'll find that many, many guilds on all the <br>
servers are only today moving through that content that you left behind 6 months or even a year ago. For them the use of knight tanks is a very viable alternative. Only a very small percentage of a server population will be always on the cutting edge. For a proper look at balance all levels of play need to be given consideration - that includes the non- EB'd level 61 player in the not-quite-so Uberguild.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Let me put it to you this way. If warriors were given a 1.5 second 'cast time' ability that generated hate, like a stun, which they could use between swings, but knights were given defensive and evasive would you be happy? As a knight, if this was done, I would feel like I was getting the better end of the deal, but perhaps this is a case of the grass being greener?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Let me ask you this in return, would you give up your spellbook in exchange for defensive/evasive? it's about as balanced as your own proposal i.e. not very <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <br>
<br>
Balance isn't in such simple 'trade off's' of abilities.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>One thing I would like to be clear about is knights consider themselves tanks. In in ideal world, I think knights and warriors should all be equally good tanks, in exp groups and on raids. Different, but equally good.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
So do I, in an ideal world. Your point was?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I am willing to settle for not being able to tank any ubermob, for the consolation that I am a bit better in exp groups.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Really? thats big of you, really it is, especially when you raid 10 hours a day so you must hardly ever exp. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Tanking an Ubermob is a neccessary job for the guild to reach it's goals it's not some <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>REALLY BIG THING</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> in many cases it's the add control on raids (Aerin'dar anyone) which truely makes or breaks the raid and guess who gets that job in my guild - it's not the warriors <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  HEY ! I want to be more desirable in exp groups on days after you guys were more important to the raid! It's only fair right?? OH ! I didn't get to tank an ubermob today! i want equal ability to main tank in a group!<br>
<br>
Really, I do find that arguement ludicrous.<br>
<br>
Everyone plays their part in guild raids, exp groups are a much less inclusive activity....and exp groups are something that everyone needs access to.<br>
<br>
It's a good thing they do leave warriors as best choice to main tank in raids otherwise Afterlife would definately be making new recruitment guidelines eh?<br>
