</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=glatius2>Glatius2</A> at: 4/13/03 9:40:15 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=iustus>Iustus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/13/03 8:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: no Glatius</span><hr size=1> I do think he has a point about the quoting thing, that is why I did not bother to respond again, at some point is just going over the same ground over and over.<br>
<br>
The most important point I wanted to make is that things are pretty close to balanced right now. It would be very easy for a change be made to make warrior taunting too good, such that they not only took over knight spots in exp groups, but also took over their spots on raids. <br>
<br>
I would like to see warriors get some sort of change to make them perceived to be more valueble in exp groups, but I do not want to see the change be so big that it changes the balance when raiding, and frankly I think that will be very very hard to do.<br>
<br>
I am just going to have to disagree with the people who think that balance raiding and balance in exp groups are separate things. I do not think it is, just as someone rightly points out, being able to solo is yet a third thing, although from a SoE perspective, since they want to discourage soloing, this is going to be less of a focus.  <br>
<br>
