</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cily>Cily</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 80<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/13/03 10:23 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://mywebpages.comcast.net/jnaggy291392mi/EQ/bubbles1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: no Glatius</span><hr size=1> My personal opinion has always been that warriors should have noticeably better mitigation, without using a disc.<br>
<br>
How they do this without screwing up current encounters I have no idea, but it should have been obvious that warriors should tank better from the beginning. Somehow that fact was missed by the development team at the time, and as sucky as it is, is not something simple to repair.<br>
<br>
I could see any significant improvement in warrior mitigation making tons of MT strat encounters trivial. Would almost need retroactive revamps to some (many?) encounters giving them &quot;PoP'esque&quot; twists to maintain the challenge.<br>
<br>
As for those that believe warriors should get improved agro, I simply cannot agree. No class should get the best of both worlds. Make holding a MOBs attention equal some amount of work is fine and in my mind welcome, but the reward for that needs to be a superior ability to deal with that attention. I am in the group of people that could care less if knights can grab agro at will, just need to make sure warriors bring something to the table to make them a viable choice in tanks.<br>
<br>
I also believe a lot of this comes from Sony's horrid itemization in EQ. I really think they screwed this up bad. So many items are either all/all or useable by all plate or whatever, which really tends to flatten the HP/AC curve pretty damn fast. Not until you hit the elemental armor do they start to make this a little better really. I wont even go into how silly I find items with like 130 HP <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>AND</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> 130 MANA. That would be fine in some cases, but it seems like every item they make like this they mirror the damn mana over, making it much more valuable to hybrids. Not only do they get the same HP from it, they get enough mana boost to easily heal themselves a few hundred more, or mitigate some serious damage with stuns or whatever. grr.<br>
<br>
They got all held up on classifying items by plate/leather/silk where instead grouping by class would have been tons easier to balance.<br>
<br>
Cily <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=harbromme>Harbromme</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/14/03 5:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: no Glatius</span><hr size=1> Cily, its not only itemization.<br>
I dont whine that a SK in my guild has 200+ more AC than myself unbuffed using a 2hs.<br>
My AC is good enough to tank Cursed, XtC, TT, Behemoth....<br>
<br>
Last saturday i was playing my 62 cleric in CoD as we had no cleric but another warrior LFG in guild.<br>
The warrior has around 150 AA's compared to the above mentioned SK with around 20 or so.<br>
Who was tanking better wasnt really the issue.<br>
The warrior has a lot of offensive 2h AA's so they made a bet if the SK could still taunt off when he started attacking at 70 percent mob health.<br>
Of course he could.<br>
Then i showed the SK how a warrior feels when he cannot get agro.<br>
With a secondary healer (65 druid) in group i loaded 4 stuns and rotated them on the next mob.<br>
Guess who couldnt get agro this time ?<br>
It was a bulbonian war rat, according to message, the stun part of the spell never took hold, so only the 300 or less damage pissed the rat off enough so sk and warrior never saw it. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=65418">Gnomb Goodbasher level 65 troll warrior</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
